============================================================
ANSWER: Based on the provided context, prompt chaining works by decomposing a task into sequential subtasks, where each step builds on previous results [2]. 

The implementation shows that it chains multiple LLM calls sequentially, passing results between steps [2]. Specifically, it takes an input and a list of prompts, then iterates through each prompt, passing the result from one step as input to the next step [2].

